Commentary: full, on off and middle stump. Comes forward to defend, and he defends, but they appeal for lbw. South Africa think it was pad-bat and not bat-pad... and wow, de Kock is convinced enough to review. Replays show that the ball was touching the bat and pad at the same time. TV umpire says 'it's not conclusive whether bat first or pad first' and therefore they will stay with the on-field decision. What's interesting is that South Africa lose another review despite the TV umpire's decision being unconclusive

Commentary: appeal for lbw, and given! Five for on Test debut Or is it? Bavuma reviews, he might as well. Full just outside off and angling in. Bavuma tries to sweep but misses, and it hits the inside-half of his front leg. UltraEdge says there is no bat involved. Ball-tracking says impact in line, hitting middle stump and what a wonderful moment for Nauman Ali! The 12th Pakistan bowler to take a five-wicket haul on Test debut. All smiles for him. Does the sajdah to celebrate the achievement. Pakistan need 88 to win
